#Text=Bill Freeman ( racing driver )
#Text=For the Canadian author , see Bill Freeman .
#Text=Bill Freeman is a professional racing driver , race team owner , motorsport racing enthusiast , race car manufacturer , and business entrepreneur .
#Text=Racing career
#Text=1961 - 1967 Go Kart racing in the Midwest .
#Text=Dual & Triple engine
#Text=S.C.C.A. Racing , Triumph TR4 , MGB , 427 Cobra [ 1 ]
#Text=1972 - 1978 S.C.C.A. Trans-Am , I.M.S.A. GT Racing , Can-Am [ 2 ] ( Corvette , Camaro , Porsche , Lola , McLaren )
#Text=1977 S.C.C.A. B-Production National Champion ( SP Division - Porsche 911RSR )
#Text=Freeman was S.C.C.A. National Champion in his 911 Porsche . [ 3 ] [ 4 ] [ 5 ] [ 6 ]
#Text=Freeman was the originator and supervisor for all aspects of a new Ferrari IMSA team . [ 7 ] [ 8 ]
#Text=Newman Freeman Racing ( Can-Am , Indy , I.M.S.A. )
#Text=Newman Freeman Racing logo
#Text=Paul Newman and Bill Freeman at Willow Springs Raceway in 1976 alongside Bill Freeman 's Porsche 911 .
#Text=In 1978 Paul Newman and Bill Freeman formed a racing partnership to compete in various forms of auto racing .
#Text=The Racing Team was based in Santa Barbara , California .
#Text=As the team 's Managing Partner , Freeman managed all aspects and operations for this professional automobile racing company .
#Text=The company specialized in Indy Cars , Can-Am , and other high-performance motorsport racing .
#Text=The team raced in Chevrolet-powered Spyder NF 's , sponsored by Budweiser .
#Text=The " Newman Freeman Racing " team dominated North America 's Can Am series in its Budweiser sponsored Lola team .

column1: #Text=The partnership attracted several drivers who would go on to become legends in the future , included Keke Rosberg , Elliott Forbes-Robinson , Bobby Rahal , Danny Sullivan , Teo Fabi , and others .
#Text=Driving for Newman Freeman Racing , these drivers won many competitions including the Can-Am Team Championship of 1979 .
#Text=Paul Newman and Bill Freeman on Princess Grace 's balcony overlooking the Monaco Grand Prix , 1979 .
#Text=Bill Freeman is credited as the man who introduced Paul Newman to professional auto racing .

#Text=In addition to the team management , Bill Freeman and Paul Newman drove many S.C.C.A. and I.M.S.A. events together , including the Sebring 12 hour endurance sports car race . [ 9 ] [ 10 ] [ 11 ]
#Text=1983-1984 Gurney Freeman Racing

#Text=Freeman was General Manager and Team Manager for Gurney Freeman Racing Indianapolis 500 CART championship racing team and partners with Dan Gurney at All American Racers in Santa Ana , California . [ 12 ] [ 13 ]
#Text=1984 – Present : Managing Partner - Newman Freeman Racing and CEO - Fine Sports Cars [ 14 ]
#Text=Other business
#Text=In 1979
#Text=Freeman also formed Fine Sports Cars with partner Ashton Marshall , to remanufacture , restore , and offer for sale legendary sports racing cars .
#Text=The company was based in San Diego , California , with a showroom , The Fine Car Store , located in La Jolla , California . [ 8 ] [ 15 ] [ 16 ]
#Text=In 2009 the company was expanded .
#Text=Freeman , Fine Sports Cars CEO , took on an additional partner Dr. Michael Prior .

#Text=Prior restructured the company operations to encompass a full range of vintage sports racing cars including both sanctioned and certified cars , established a global network of workshops and suppliers , and established a regional office in Europe . [ 14 ] [ 17 ]
#Text=Awards
#Text=Freeman was S.C.C.A. National Champion in his 911 Porsche in 1977 [ 18 ]
#Text=Newman Freeman Racing won the Can-Am Team championship
#Text=Freeman co-managed the race team which Paul Newman drove for in the 24 hours of Le Mans class winning victory in 1979
#Text=AAR Gurney Freeman Racing set the fastest stock block qualifying lap in history for the 1982 Indianapolis 500 [ 13 ]
